				\begin{document}$$t=sqrt\left( N\right) \times 0.5$$\end{document}t=sqrtN×0.5 , where N is the number of subjects, in our case 38, and 0.5 is the Cohen’s coefficient. Finally, for each contrast (meditators > controls and meditators < controls), topological clusters of structural links that showed significant differences (\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
